•  Could not access Witherspoon 1974 full text. Only bibliographic metadata and citations in secondary sources were available. All claims about Witherspoon 1974 are mediated through Witherspoon 1977 and later citations.
•  No peer-reviewed source dedicated exclusively to Navajo "love." The extraction relies on inference from kinship studies (Witherspoon), wellness philosophy (Kahn-John), and legal commentary (Austin/Yazzie). This is a documented absence, not a gap filled by speculation.
Cross-Tradition Lineage Flags
•  None identified. No source claims Navajo k'é or hózhó was shaped by or feeds into another tradition in the project's eight-tradition set. Navajo philosophy is presented as autochthonous, though scholars note structural parallels with other Indigenous relational ontologies.
